<%#
  Shared "Work with me" CTA block -- terminal-identity redesign (#1226): a bordered
  "# get in touch" card (Home's in-page CTA, About's contact card). No longer rendered
  inside the site footer (the footer carries its own identity/sitemap/newsletter
  columns only, per the redesign's Shared chrome spec); each page renders its own copy
  of this card instead.

  Call shape:
    render "components/work_with_me_cta"
    render "components/work_with_me_cta", supporting_copy: "Custom supporting sentence."

  Locals:
    supporting_copy: optional -- overrides the default supporting sentence

  href is sourced from resume_data[:basics][:email] (resume/resume.yml) so a future
  form or booking URL is a one-line swap here. The visible label now matches the design
  reference exactly -- "[ work with me ]", brackets and all -- via cta_button's
  aria_label local, which keeps the accessible name "Work with me" for assistive tech
  rather than reading the bracket punctuation aloud.
%>
<%
  default_copy = "Have a hard technical decision in front of you, or a team that could use an outside perspective?"
  copy = local_assigns[:supporting_copy] || default_copy
%>
<div class="border border-base-300 bg-base-200 rounded-[10px] p-7 md:p-8 flex items-center gap-8 flex-wrap font-mono">
  <div class="flex-1 min-w-[280px]">
    <p class="text-[13px] text-primary mb-1.5"># get in touch</p>
    <p class="font-sans text-lg text-base-content/70 m-0"><%= copy %></p>
  </div>
  <%= render "components/cta_button", label: "[ work with me ]", aria_label: "Work with me", href: "mailto:#{resume_data[:basics][:email]}", style: :primary %>
</div>
